data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 11 / EF Core 11, the **sync-over-async compatibility shim for the Cosmos DB provider is removed entirely**. The opt-in you configured in .NET 10 (e.g., `EnableSyncOverAsync()`) no longer exists.

All synchronous LINQ operators (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` will throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime — with **no way to opt back in**.

## The Fix

Convert to async equivalents:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- This only affects the **Cosmos DB provider** — the relational providers still support sync operations.
- The Cosmos SDK has always been async-only; the shim was always a temporary bridge.
- You'll need to propagate `async/await` up through your call chain (controllers, services, etc.).
